The paper discusses the challenges of mobile media delivery and proposes solutions that involve both networking and multimedia aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses multimedia-related topics such as video quality planning and content prefetching, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) is another likely category. The paper also discusses self-organizing functionalities and context signaling, which are related to system-level control and optimization, suggesting that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category. The paper also discusses energy efficiency and resource allocation, which are related to security and privacy, suggesting that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses cross-layer optimization, which is related to distributed computing, suggesting that cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category.
